HEADWORD: Cepheus
<hw>Ce"pheus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<def>A northern constellation near the pole. Its head, which is in the
Milky Way, is marked by a triangle formed by three stars of the fourth
magnitude. See <er>Cassiopeia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cepphus</ent>⟦br⟧
